  "text": "Community composition driven by species interaction assumes that species with similar niches do not co-exist because they share the same resources, predators, or pathogens [CITATION_1] . Therefore, this process is simulated by removing one of two species from the regional species pool that show the highest similarity in their traits or taxonomy (Fig. 2c) .",
